comments: Registration restricted to Computer Science, Cybersecurity In Computer Science, and Data Analytics majors only. Overview of Linux environments, GUI & Command Terminal. Important commands for information & action commands. Linux file system hierarchy. Filesystem backup & recovery. Security and ethics. Linux system and user administration. Custom user environment. Powerful and programmable text editing tools. Complex sort and search functions. Bash special functions. Bash script programming. Make and software management with Makefile scripts. Overview of more powerful commands and techniques for large-scale system administration, software development, and software maintenance unique to Linux. Rigorous coverage & practice of all skills needed by users and system administrators.
